# Phase 2: Spring Security + Authentication API

## Overview

Wire JWT-based stateless auth on top of the existing User/Role entities. Three roles: `ROLE_ADMIN`, `ROLE_CUSTOMER`, `ROLE_BUSINESS`.

## Proposed Changes

### Security Package (`com.virtbank.security`)

#### [NEW] JwtUtils.java
- `generateToken(userId, email, role)` → signed HS256 JWT via jjwt
- `validateToken(token)` → boolean
- `extractEmail(token)`, `extractUserId(token)` — claim getters
- Reads `app.jwt.secret` and `app.jwt.expiration-ms` from properties

#### [NEW] JwtAuthFilter.java
- `OncePerRequestFilter` — reads `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
- Validates via JwtUtils, loads `UserDetails`, sets `SecurityContext`

#### [NEW] UserDetailsServiceImpl.java
- Implements `UserDetailsService`, loads by email via [UserRepository](file:///d:/javaproj/src/main/java/com/virtbank/repository/UserRepository.java#14-34)
- Maps User's M2M Role set → `GrantedAuthority` list (e.g. `ROLE_CUSTOMER`)

---

### Config Package (`com.virtbank.config`)

#### [NEW] SecurityConfig.java
- `@EnableMethodSecurity` for `@PreAuthorize`
- Disable CSRF, stateless sessions
- Permit: `/api/auth/**`, `/swagger-ui/**`, `/api-docs/**`
- All other endpoints require authentication
- Registers `JwtAuthFilter` before `UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter`
- Beans: `BCryptPasswordEncoder`, `AuthenticationManager`

---

### DTO Package (`com.virtbank.dto`)

#### [NEW] RegisterRequest.java
Fields: `firstName`, `lastName`, `email`, `password`, `phone`, `userType` (with `@NotBlank`/`@Email` validation)

#### [NEW] LoginRequest.java
Fields: `email`, `password`

#### [NEW] AuthResponse.java
Fields: `token`, `userId`, `email`, `role`

---

### Controller Package (`com.virtbank.controller`)

#### [NEW] AuthController.java
- `POST /api/auth/register` — validate, hash password, save user w/ role, return JWT
- `POST /api/auth/login` — authenticate via `AuthenticationManager`, return JWT

#### [NEW] TestController.java
- `GET /api/test/public` — open endpoint
- `GET /api/test/customer` — `@PreAuthorize("hasRole('CUSTOMER')")`
- `GET /api/test/admin` — `@PreAuthorize("hasRole('ADMIN')")`

---

### Exception Package (`com.virtbank.exception`)

#### [NEW] GlobalExceptionHandler.java
- Catches: `BadCredentialsException` → 401, `UsernameNotFoundException` → 401, `MethodArgumentNotValidException` → 400, generic `Exception` → 500
- Returns JSON: `{ "status": 401, "error": "...", "message": "...", "timestamp": "..." }`

#### [NEW] ErrorResponse.java
DTO for error JSON body.

